  "description": "This dataset comprises electroencephalography recordings from 16 participants viewing object images presented at eight different two-dimensional rotations in rapid visual streams. Stimuli were presented at two distinct rates (5 Hz and 20 Hz) to investigate rotation-tolerant neural representations and elucidate the temporal dynamics of high-level object processing in the human brain.",
  "methods_description": "EEG recordings were collected from 16 participants viewing object images in eight different 2-D rotations presented in rapid visual streams at two presentation rates (5 Hz and 20 Hz). Data are provided in standard BIDS format.",
